Both required outputs are in place and validated.

**`transcript.json`** — 25 iterations conforming to schema; covers:
- Iter 1–8: outcome scoping, univariate scan, main prognostic effects, multivariable adjusted model
- Iter 9–10: joint adverse profile and smoking × histology interactions
- Iter 11–12: candidate treatment identification + interaction screen across all candidates
- Iter 13–18: discovery and confirmation of the central treatment-heterogeneity finding
- Iter 19–23: null-result candidate treatments, T-learner CATE validation, sensitivity walks
- Iter 24–25: consolidated multivariable interaction model and final subgroup hypothesis

**`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative synthesis.

**Headline finding:** feature_018 is a treatment whose benefit is confined to the subgroup defined by **feature_016 == 1 AND feature_031 == 0 AND feature_028 == 0 AND feature_005 == 0** (n=3,266). In-subgroup effect ≈ **+4.99 months PFS** (p ≈ 0); out-of-subgroup effect ≈ −0.006 mo (p = 0.76). Each of feature_031==1, feature_028==1, feature_005==1 individually abolishes the benefit when feature_016==1. The candidate-treatment binaries with null univariate effects (feature_002/012/020/027) showed no meaningful subgroup heterogeneity on exhaustive search and behave as noise.
